Implement Phase 2 (Solution Proposals): each model proposes ranked solutions with sub-components and property tags (e.g. approaches A/B for component X, C/D for component Y). Implement Phase 3 (Voting): present all solutions to all available models, each ranks complete combinations (e.g. [A+D, A+C, B+D, B+C]), tally votes across models, determine winning combination, handle ties by preferring simpler/more conservative solution. AC: Models propose solutions with property tags. Voting produces ranked combination list. Ties resolved conservatively.